CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 8, 1962, pg. 28, reads: "Archers Ready for Grind - From these 11 candidates, Coach George Cupples (upper right) hopes to mould the 1962-1963 Fifth Avenue High School basketball team. Gazing up at a Courier cameraman above the basket, left to right (front row), are: Edward Ellis, Reginald Mathis, Eugene Jones. Second row: Raymond Outlaw, Deward LeMar, Robert Randall, Robert Fleming, Regis Simpson. Third row: Melvin Jackson, Eddie Matthews, Rodland Jones."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Fifth Avenue High School basketball team, front row from left: Edward Ellis, Reginald Mathis, Eugene Jones; second row: Raymond Outlaw, Deward LeMar or Eddie Lamar, Robert Randall, Robert Fleming, Regis Simpson [Sharif]; third row: Melvin Jackson, Eddie Matthews, Rodland Jones, and Coach George Cupples, posed in Fifth Avenue High School gymnasium
